<TITLE> Decision next week on 20,000 NBR cases </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 1 (bdnews24.com)The law ministry will decide next week the fate of over 20,000 cases filed by the National Board of Revenue pending with the court. NBR chairman Nasiruddin Ahmed met with law minister Shafique Ahmed on Thursday and urged him to take initiative to dispose of the cases. "Over 20,000 cases filed by NBR have been awaiting disposal in different courts," the law minister told the reporters after the meeting at the Secretariat. "How the cases will be promptly disposed of will be finalised after a meeting with NBR and relevant authorities next week." The law minister said, the steps, if necessary, would be made either through amendment of law or through forming a separate bench. The NBR chief said, "The disposal of the pending cases will pave the way for revenue earning of Tk 6,000 crore." He said he had talks with the law minister as an initial step. b
